			<title>REVOLUTION.COM: A Conversation with Patricia Seybold, founder and lead visionary, the Patricia Seybold Group</title>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Enterpriseleadership-Audios/~3/62HuSQ9Wa_Y/EL_patti_seybold_2005_06_09.mp3</link>
            <description>"It is always the simple that produces the marvelous" -- Amelia Barr. In 1998, a woman named Patricia Seybold authored a book, customers.com, followed a few years later by The Customer Revolution. These two books crystallized all the rampant requisites of dot.com-era eBusiness into one, simple tenet: Know who your customers are and make sure you have the products and services they want. Seybold’s refreshingly straightforward thoughts about customer service, along with the compelling case histories she presented made a lasting impression on the burgeoning landscape of eCommerce. In this exclusive interview with EnterpriseLeadership.org, Patricia Seybold talks about how the landscape of doing business via the Internet has changed -- and how it has not changed -- in the seven years since her first book's publication.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Enterpriseleadership-Audios/~4/62HuSQ9Wa_Y" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description>
